# Portal

This component is used to render content at the end of the document body.
Portal is used in IDS components: Drawer, ModalDialog, Position, and ZIndex.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/portal
```

```tsx
import { Portal } from '@ids-ts/portal';
```

## Props API

| Prop | Type | Required | Description |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| `children` | `React.ReactNode` | Yes | * The elements to render inside the portal container |
| `id` | `string` | No | * ID attribute to attach to the DOM element representing the portal |
| `ownerDocument` | `Document | null` | No | * owner document inside which portal element has to be placed |

<details>
<summary>Full TypeScript Interface</summary>

```typescript
export interface PortalProps {
  /**
   * The elements to render inside the portal container
   */
  children: React.ReactNode;
  /**
   * ID attribute to attach to the DOM element representing the portal
   */
  id?: string;
  /**
   * owner document inside which portal element has to be placed
   */
